-- Berkshire Employee Count Climbs to About 270,000 With Lubrizol
-- B y   A n d r e w   F r y e
-- 2012-01-24T15:13:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-24/berkshire-employee-count-climbs-to-about-270-000-with-lubrizol.html
Berkshire Hathaway Inc. (BRK/A) ’s employee
count increased by about 9,500 since the end of 2010 as Chairman
 Warren Buffett  added engine-additives maker Lubrizol Corp.  Berkshire has about 270,000 employees, the Omaha, Nebraska-
based company said today in a regulatory filing tied to a bond
offering. That compares with the 260,519 figure in Berkshire’s
2010 annual report. Lubrizol had about 6,900 workers at the end
of 2010.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrew Frye in New York at 
